WEBVTT

00:01.168 --> 00:03.298
[ALL SHOUTING]

00:03.469 --> 00:05.440
HARRY:
Settle down.

00:07.206 --> 00:09.536
Okay. settle down!

00:09.708 --> 00:13.668
Settle down! Settle--!
Quiet. quiet. quiet!

00:14.113 --> 00:17.053
Now. here's the situation.
We have four women in active labor...

00:17.216 --> 00:20.016
...and we have lost all communication
with the outside world!

00:20.186 --> 00:23.276
I want all non-court personnel
out of here!

00:23.456 --> 00:24.746
Are there any questions?

00:25.657 --> 00:27.277
Yes?

00:27.559 --> 00:30.459
Why is the sky blue?

00:34.766 --> 00:38.956
Because if it was green.
we wouldn't know where to stop mowing.

00:41.039 --> 00:43.839
Any others? Then get moving. people!

00:45.877 --> 00:46.897
-Mac.
MAC: Yo.

00:47.078 --> 00:49.068
-Get bandages. blankets. cotton and string.
-Right.

00:49.247 --> 00:50.437
-Miss Sullivan.
CHRISTINE: Sir?

00:50.615 --> 00:53.345
What the hell am I gonna do
with all that stuff that Mac brings?

00:54.219 --> 00:56.239
I got the windows boarded up.
What should I do now?

00:56.420 --> 00:58.510
We might need your help
with the deliveries.

00:58.689 --> 01:01.419
Right. I'll go boil my tools.

01:02.326 --> 01:04.656
Great. That torque wrench
might come in handy.

01:05.328 --> 01:07.389
Your Honor. I found a medical book.

01:07.564 --> 01:10.834
Now. there's a chapter
on emergency child deliveries.

01:11.001 --> 01:13.801
-Great. Make four copies of that.
-I'll get right on it.

01:13.971 --> 01:15.001
-Flo.
-What?

01:15.172 --> 01:19.702
-What's the first thing it says to do?
-Uh. "Keep the mother from panicking."

01:19.877 --> 01:22.437
[SCREAMING]

01:24.848 --> 01:28.808
God. let's hope
they're all that considerate.

01:30.000 --> 01:36.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

02:12.629 --> 02:14.459
Don't worry. baby. I'm right here.

02:14.631 --> 02:15.791
[MARY SIGHS]

02:15.965 --> 02:18.955
Bull. what is this woman doing
laying on the salad bar?

02:19.135 --> 02:21.755
Uh. the tables were too hard.

02:21.938 --> 02:25.568
I guess I should've taken out
that Jell-O mold. huh?

02:26.708 --> 02:27.728
[MARY GROANS]

02:27.909 --> 02:30.399
-Hey. come on. somebody do something.
-Take it easy. Stanley.

02:30.579 --> 02:33.109
Take it easy? She's in severe labor pains.

02:33.281 --> 02:36.811
No. no. no. it's just some radishes
sticking me in the back.

02:38.019 --> 02:40.849
Here's the instructions.
I'm afraid you guys are on your own.

02:41.022 --> 02:45.792
Don't worry. sir.
Remember. we're professional bailiffs.

02:46.261 --> 02:49.161
Yeah. that ought to put
their minds at ease.

02:49.798 --> 02:50.888
[GROANS]

02:51.066 --> 02:53.056
Something's happening.

02:53.234 --> 02:55.834
Okay. Flo. Read them off.

02:56.003 --> 03:00.573
-"Remove any restrictive clothing."
-Right.

03:04.110 --> 03:07.170
-I think they mean her.
-Oh. yeah.

03:07.347 --> 03:09.247
Oh. uh-uh.

03:09.415 --> 03:12.605
Nobody's looking at my wife's private parts
except me.

03:12.785 --> 03:14.575
Some things are still sacred.

03:14.754 --> 03:18.354
Well. if it were sacred.
she wouldn't be in this mess now.

03:18.791 --> 03:23.061
-My answer is no.
-Fine. Then you deliver the baby.

03:28.034 --> 03:29.374
[CRASH]

03:33.272 --> 03:34.502
Men.

03:34.673 --> 03:38.913
When you want them down. they're up.
When you want them up. they're down.

03:40.278 --> 03:41.338
[ELENA SCREAMS]

03:41.513 --> 03:44.313
[SPEAKING IN SPANISH]

03:44.483 --> 03:46.613
Push. Mrs. Chacone. push.

03:46.785 --> 03:48.875
Do you have any children. Miss Sullivan?

03:49.554 --> 03:50.584
No.

03:51.690 --> 03:53.820
Ever had a man?

03:56.094 --> 03:58.724
Of course I've had a man.

03:58.897 --> 04:02.087
If I had a nickel for every man I'd had...

04:03.368 --> 04:05.858
...I'd have a dime.

04:08.940 --> 04:10.430
-Here.
CHRISTINE: Okay.

04:10.609 --> 04:12.979
-Aah! Look!
-What is it. Miss Sullivan?

04:13.145 --> 04:16.135
Good Lord. he's a virgin.

04:17.548 --> 04:18.809
It's the baby.

04:18.983 --> 04:20.353
qué?

04:20.517 --> 04:22.508
-Tell him it's the baby.
-It's the baby.

04:24.822 --> 04:28.222
-Bob.
-And his name is Bob.

04:31.127 --> 04:33.457
What a coincidence.

04:34.297 --> 04:36.427
-Bob.
-Which one?

04:36.933 --> 04:39.873
Tell him. in Spanish.
that his baby is coming.

04:40.036 --> 04:41.626
Yes. sir. Paco:

04:41.804 --> 04:44.214
[SPEAKS IN SPANISH]

04:44.373 --> 04:45.403
[SPEAKS IN SPANISH]

04:45.574 --> 04:46.604
si.

04:47.242 --> 04:50.142
[SPEAKS IN SPANISH]

04:53.648 --> 04:55.078
[SCREAMSI

04:55.249 --> 04:56.879
Shh! Shh! Shh!

04:57.051 --> 04:59.491
-Who you telling to shush?
-[STAMMERS] I'm sorry. I just--

04:59.654 --> 05:01.954
Try pulling a Cabbage Patch doll
through your nostril...

05:02.122 --> 05:05.022
...and see what kind of sound you make.

05:06.493 --> 05:09.293
That's it. Just let it all out.

05:09.463 --> 05:11.933
Argh! If you don't like it. you can leave.

05:12.099 --> 05:14.969
-I told you before. I don't need anyone.
-Oh. fine.

05:15.135 --> 05:19.465
I'll go get you a mirror and some
salad tongs and you can do this yourself.

05:19.639 --> 05:20.939
I think it's coming.

05:21.107 --> 05:22.577
-Instructions.
-Thank you.

05:24.110 --> 05:27.170
-Tommy. get me some surgical gloves.
-Uh, from where?

05:27.346 --> 05:28.776
My briefcase, top pocket.

05:33.352 --> 05:35.342
Great. Now I can deduct them.

05:35.755 --> 05:37.305
[THUNDER CRASHING]

05:37.490 --> 05:38.510
[BABS YELLS]

05:38.691 --> 05:40.991
Babs. honey. describe for us
exactly what you're feeling...

05:41.159 --> 05:42.719
...at this crucial moment in your life.

05:43.628 --> 05:46.828
I want you dead, Chad.

05:47.866 --> 05:50.626
Chad, maybe let the girl be, huh?
She's obviously exhausted.

05:50.802 --> 05:55.142
They told us in class that under this stress.
a woman can say outrageous things.

05:55.306 --> 05:57.096
Things totally alien to her character.

05:57.275 --> 06:04.175
I hate my Volvo! I want a Trans Am!

06:04.916 --> 06:08.076
Gee. it still doesn't prepare you
for the shock. though.

06:08.820 --> 06:12.280
-Mrs. Ulin.
-Babs, I'm not Mrs. Anybody.

06:12.457 --> 06:17.547
We chose not to burden ourselves
with any archaic commitments. remember?

06:17.729 --> 06:19.029
Like a baby?

06:19.563 --> 06:23.063
She, uh, mistook a Tic Tac for her pill.

06:23.700 --> 06:25.130
[GROANING]

06:25.302 --> 06:27.702
Here comes another one.

06:27.871 --> 06:30.601
Here. here. you can hold on
to my ears. Sure.

06:30.774 --> 06:34.114
[BOTH SCREAMING]

06:37.147 --> 06:39.547
I'm sorry. honey.
I swear. it won't happen again.

06:39.716 --> 06:44.236
Stanley has such a delicate system.
Gets out of whack when he's excited.

06:44.421 --> 06:48.091
He even faints
when the Giants score a touchdown.

06:48.425 --> 06:51.155
So does their coach.

06:51.328 --> 06:52.758
Whoa!

06:52.930 --> 06:53.950
[MARY PANTING]

06:54.131 --> 06:57.031
Here's baby.

06:57.401 --> 06:58.991
Oh, wow!

06:59.168 --> 07:03.038
He's coming!
Mary. baby Bubba is coming!

07:03.206 --> 07:07.196
You're naming your son Bubba?

07:08.343 --> 07:12.143
We arm-wrestled for it.
My choice was Bing.

07:12.314 --> 07:14.284
I think I'm gonna cry.

07:14.449 --> 07:16.349
[MARY SCREAMS]

07:16.518 --> 07:19.038
Here he comes. here he comes.

07:19.221 --> 07:22.661
Look at the grin on that kid's face.

07:25.226 --> 07:26.916
Bull.

07:32.433 --> 07:34.963
That's not his face.

07:39.039 --> 07:41.769
And that ain't no grin.

07:43.377 --> 07:44.997
It's not?

07:45.613 --> 07:48.513
Hey, he's backing out.

07:49.350 --> 07:53.750
-It's a breach baby?
-A breach baby!

07:53.921 --> 07:56.481
Stay on your feet. Stanley.
or I'll knock you cold.

07:56.657 --> 07:58.987
Flo, Flo, look it up.

07:59.159 --> 08:02.289
Yeah. Okay. here it is.
Breach birth. breach birth.

08:02.463 --> 08:09.063
Uh. "A natural delivery is still quite probable
with a little guidance.

08:09.703 --> 08:12.903
Gently insert...."

08:17.945 --> 08:20.135
Sit. Stanley.

08:21.448 --> 08:22.468
[ELENA PANTING]

08:22.650 --> 08:24.140
Okay, Elena, One more push.

08:24.318 --> 08:25.338
[PACO SPEAKING IN SPANISH]

08:25.519 --> 08:26.679
[ELENA GROANS]

08:27.086 --> 08:28.106
It's out.

08:28.288 --> 08:29.718
[ELENA PANTS]

08:29.889 --> 08:33.379
Okay. Uh. now I drain the mouth.

08:34.894 --> 08:36.494
[BABY CRYING]

08:36.662 --> 08:38.652
Oh, thank God.

08:38.830 --> 08:40.059
It's a girl.

08:40.231 --> 08:41.431
qué?

08:41.599 --> 08:43.029
Paco.

08:43.200 --> 08:48.400
Baby Bob es él transsexual.

08:49.473 --> 08:50.573
[ELENA SCREAMS]

08:50.741 --> 08:54.941
-What's the matter?
-I think we got another bun in the oven.

08:55.112 --> 08:57.442
-qué?
-Another baby.

08:57.615 --> 08:58.805
qué?

08:59.417 --> 09:01.477
Dos babies.

09:01.652 --> 09:05.182
Oh, no, Bob?

09:06.557 --> 09:09.357
Let's pray this one's normal.

09:10.061 --> 09:13.221
-Oh, my God! Oh, my God!
-What's wrong?

09:13.397 --> 09:16.697
How the hell should I know?
I'm just a general practitioner.

09:17.234 --> 09:20.674
-Fielding, get over here.
-Coming, dear.

09:20.838 --> 09:23.808
-Tommy, get behind the plate.
-Me?

09:24.374 --> 09:27.744
-What do I do?
-If something comes out, catch it.

09:32.215 --> 09:33.375
-Dan.
-What?

09:33.549 --> 09:35.179
Dan. I lied to you.

09:35.351 --> 09:38.691
You gonna tell me
this is just an incredible simulation?

09:38.854 --> 09:42.224
I mean about not wanting anybody.

09:43.092 --> 09:44.562
Dan.

09:44.727 --> 09:46.987
Dan. Dan. I'm scared.

09:47.162 --> 09:48.822
[BOTH SCREAM]

09:50.465 --> 09:53.695
-Dan. I just don't wanna be alone.
-No. you're not. you're not. you're not.

09:53.868 --> 09:55.728
Listen. Shh. shh. shh. You're not alone.

09:55.903 --> 09:57.503
I'm here. I'm here.

09:57.671 --> 10:00.871
I'll stay here until the end. all right?

10:01.074 --> 10:04.074
Now just remove your teeth
from my chest...

10:05.445 --> 10:07.675
...and we'll continue.

10:08.949 --> 10:11.539
HARRY: It's coming. It's coming.
Something's coming. I can see it.

10:11.717 --> 10:14.907
-Could we tighten up the group just a bit?
-Yeah, how's this?

10:15.087 --> 10:18.487
Oh. fine. I got everybody now.

10:18.656 --> 10:19.676
Okay. Babs.

10:19.858 --> 10:21.218
[BABS & HARRY PANTING]

10:21.392 --> 10:22.832
[ALL GRUNTING]

10:24.128 --> 10:26.928
-Chad!
-Sweetheart?

10:27.097 --> 10:30.227
I wanna get married!

10:30.401 --> 10:33.231
Wow. what a reaction shot.

10:33.404 --> 10:36.004
-Babs, you what?
-I wanna get married.

10:36.172 --> 10:38.642
Bit I thought you always hated marriage
as an institution.

10:38.808 --> 10:40.868
I just said that
because you felt that way.

10:41.044 --> 10:43.214
I just said that because
I thought you felt that way.

10:43.378 --> 10:45.708
-Oh, you mean you want to?
-Marry you? Yes.

10:45.881 --> 10:47.281
Oh. Oh.

10:47.449 --> 10:48.939
Judge, could you marry us?

10:50.451 --> 10:52.941
I'm kind of busy right now.

10:53.120 --> 10:56.580
Oh, please, sir, don't let our baby
be born out of wedlock.

10:59.692 --> 11:01.562
-Mac?
-Yes?

11:04.063 --> 11:06.363
Fix my hair a little, huh?

11:10.868 --> 11:12.428
[THUNDER CRASHES]

11:12.603 --> 11:15.103
[BABY CRYING]

11:16.107 --> 11:17.507
It's a girl.

11:18.209 --> 11:21.039
Wait till she hears about her brother.

11:22.113 --> 11:24.953
[SPEAKING IN SPANISH]

11:27.618 --> 11:28.948
[SCREAMS]

11:29.120 --> 11:32.090
-Oh, no.
-Oh, yes.

11:32.255 --> 11:34.985
What is this, a vending machine?

11:36.693 --> 11:38.823
All right.
Now. we need one more big push.

11:38.995 --> 11:41.895
-I can't. I can't. I can't.
-Yes. you can. You can.

11:42.466 --> 11:44.956
Think about Hugh Hefner.

11:45.135 --> 11:46.655
[BENAY GROWLING]

11:46.836 --> 11:47.856
It's coming.

11:49.071 --> 11:52.561
Sitting there in his silk pajamas with
all these big-breasted. exploited women...

11:52.741 --> 11:54.801
...catering to his every whim.

11:54.977 --> 11:56.467
[GROWLING]

11:56.645 --> 11:59.635
-I can see a shoulder.
-Wait. Who's that coming through the door?

11:59.815 --> 12:01.505
Oh, look, it is. It's Bobby Riggs.

12:01.684 --> 12:03.084
[SNARLING]

12:03.252 --> 12:05.522
-It's out.
-Yes.

12:05.821 --> 12:07.311
-Clean out its mouth.
-With what?

12:07.490 --> 12:09.930
Oh, for Pete's sake, here.

12:10.559 --> 12:11.859
[BABY CRYING]

12:12.026 --> 12:14.046
Oh. Oh, what is it?

12:14.228 --> 12:16.318
It's a baby.

12:17.231 --> 12:19.221
And it's naked.

12:19.399 --> 12:21.369
It's a boy.

12:21.535 --> 12:23.825
He's got a promising future.

12:26.873 --> 12:29.273
How about that? We had a baby.

12:29.442 --> 12:32.242
-"We" had it?
-Hey.

12:32.411 --> 12:35.041
You couldn't have done it alone.

12:35.948 --> 12:39.378
You're right. I couldn't have.

12:40.119 --> 12:42.279
[BOTH CHUCKLE]

12:42.454 --> 12:44.324
-Let me see him.
-First, I gotta cut the cord.

12:44.489 --> 12:47.189
-Uh, boy scout knife?
-Top-left pocket.

12:48.593 --> 12:50.323
Oh, Mom.

12:55.065 --> 12:57.725
First. I'll cut his, then yours.

12:58.602 --> 13:00.572
[MARY GRUNTING]

13:00.738 --> 13:02.998
-The head's coming now.
-A head?

13:03.174 --> 13:05.204
He's got a head.

13:06.242 --> 13:07.272
It's almost out.

13:07.443 --> 13:09.883
-Somebody give me a blanket.
-We don't have one.

13:10.046 --> 13:11.066
Oh.

13:11.247 --> 13:15.077
-Here. Use this.
-The New York Times?

13:15.250 --> 13:18.580
The book says that a fresh newspaper
is very sanitary.

13:18.754 --> 13:22.384
Well. okay. but use the Sports section.

13:23.692 --> 13:26.092
You already bought him a mitt.
didn't you?

13:35.504 --> 13:39.704
-What's happening?
-Somebody's having a baby.

13:40.642 --> 13:43.112
[BABY CRYING]

13:43.278 --> 13:45.798
Eureka!

13:45.981 --> 13:48.081
Bubba.

13:48.850 --> 13:51.840
Better make that Bubbette.

13:52.721 --> 13:54.991
-I beg your pardon?
-It's a girl.

13:55.490 --> 13:58.550
No. No, it can't be.

13:58.727 --> 14:01.197
I got pictures.

14:01.363 --> 14:04.763
I'd clean that lens if I were you.

14:07.668 --> 14:10.328
-Marriage license.
-Oh. the ceremony.

14:10.504 --> 14:12.304
Sir, look, sir, you gotta sign this.

14:12.473 --> 14:15.603
Mac. I am holding a fragile human life
in my hands.

14:17.378 --> 14:19.438
Put the pen in my mouth.

14:20.381 --> 14:21.411
Is this legal?

14:21.582 --> 14:24.482
[HARRY MUTTERING INDISTINCTLY]

14:26.119 --> 14:28.819
"Howie Stallone."

14:29.055 --> 14:30.105
Close enough. Pen.

14:30.290 --> 14:31.720
-Ceremony.
-Yeah. yeah. yeah.

14:31.891 --> 14:35.621
-Dearly beloved-- I got an arm.
-Whoa. Hurry. please.

14:35.795 --> 14:36.815
Okay. Bottom line.

14:36.997 --> 14:40.257
Babs Townsend. do you take this man
to be your lawfully wedded husband?

14:40.433 --> 14:42.803
[SCREAMING]

14:44.536 --> 14:46.596
-Is that a yes?
-Yes.

14:46.772 --> 14:49.402
Okay. Hey. Chad Ulin. Chad--

14:49.575 --> 14:51.095
-And there's another arm.
-Sir?

14:51.276 --> 14:52.736
-He's coming.
-Sir?

14:52.910 --> 14:55.710
-Okay. do you wanna marry her or what?
-Yes.

14:55.880 --> 14:58.780
Then by the power vested in me
by the state. I pronounce you man and wife.

14:58.950 --> 15:00.180
It's a boy!

15:00.350 --> 15:02.110
[ALL YELLING]

15:07.658 --> 15:09.788
Are you that disappointed. Stanley?

15:10.494 --> 15:13.364
This must be your appendix
or something.

15:13.730 --> 15:15.530
-You wanna hold your daughter?
-Me?

15:15.699 --> 15:17.459
No. no. I might break it or something.

15:17.634 --> 15:19.104
-I don't think so.
-No. no. Hey. wait.

15:19.269 --> 15:21.239
-I don't know what I'm doing.
-Yes. you do.

15:21.405 --> 15:23.865
Look at you. just like a pro.

15:24.408 --> 15:27.468
Well, aren't you gonna look at her?

15:27.644 --> 15:29.644
[BABY CRYING]

15:32.049 --> 15:33.919
Little wrinkly, isn't it?

15:34.918 --> 15:37.848
I think she'll outgrow that.

15:39.256 --> 15:44.216
-Do you love her, Stanley?
-Well, that's a stupid question.

15:44.394 --> 15:47.024
Of course I love her.

15:50.901 --> 15:53.531
She's Daddy's little girl.

15:56.673 --> 15:59.203
Hey, let's call her Hacksaw.

16:02.179 --> 16:03.739
HARRY:
Oh.

16:05.449 --> 16:06.469
-You know. Mac?
-Yeah.

16:06.650 --> 16:08.280
Someday I may have a son of my own.

16:08.452 --> 16:09.482
-Oh, yeah?
-Oh, yeah.

16:09.653 --> 16:12.153
-You don't say.
-Uh-huh.

16:20.731 --> 16:25.291
-Sir? Sir. are you all right?
-Um....

16:28.939 --> 16:30.529
Yeah.

16:30.706 --> 16:32.466
Yeah. I'm fine.

16:32.641 --> 16:35.801
Why don't you fix me a nice stiff Bosco.
huh. Mac?

16:35.978 --> 16:37.968
Coming right up. sir.

16:40.449 --> 16:41.679
[SIGHS]

16:44.886 --> 16:48.646
[PACO SPEAKING IN SPANISH]

16:50.191 --> 16:52.661
[THUNDER CRASHES]

16:52.827 --> 16:55.517
Nope. That's all she wrote.

16:55.697 --> 16:58.627
-Three beautiful girls.
-qué?

16:59.000 --> 17:03.300
[SPEAKING IN SPANISH]

17:03.738 --> 17:05.538
Gracias.

17:06.241 --> 17:08.011
[SPEAKS IN SPANISH]

17:08.175 --> 17:10.136
Oh, good luck. Mr. Chacone.

17:10.310 --> 17:13.941
And God bless
your beautiful little babies.

17:14.115 --> 17:16.075
Rosalita.

17:16.751 --> 17:18.911
Lucinda.

17:20.087 --> 17:22.317
And Gummo.

17:23.757 --> 17:26.156
I suggested that.

17:26.926 --> 17:29.827
It's Granny's nickname.

17:34.101 --> 17:36.401
[SPEAKS IN SPANISH]

17:36.569 --> 17:38.559
[SPEAKING IN SPANISH]

17:41.307 --> 17:42.467
What'd she say?

17:42.641 --> 17:46.011
“I love you, Paco, with all my heart."

17:46.178 --> 17:48.038
[SPEAKS IN SPANISH]

17:48.213 --> 17:51.053
"But touch me again...

17:52.684 --> 17:54.684
[SPEAKS IN SPANISH]

17:55.320 --> 17:58.190
...and it's Soprano City."

18:01.159 --> 18:03.719
Thank you. Dan.

18:04.563 --> 18:06.163
With all my heart.

18:06.330 --> 18:08.770
I'll never forget you for this.

18:08.933 --> 18:12.273
-You'll forget me.
-Oh, no, I won't.

18:12.436 --> 18:15.926
Because I'm gonna name my son
after you.

18:17.841 --> 18:19.071
Benay.

18:19.241 --> 18:23.611
Your caring and honesty
will live with me always.

18:25.514 --> 18:26.614
[DAN SIGHS]

18:26.782 --> 18:29.312
Caring, maybe. Honesty....

18:31.152 --> 18:32.422
What are you trying to say?

18:35.590 --> 18:37.610
I lied too.

18:41.228 --> 18:43.628
Dan is not my real name.

18:46.833 --> 18:49.133
I assumed it when I started school.

18:49.301 --> 18:52.531
You see. my parents were slightly rural.

18:52.705 --> 18:54.295
Pfft. Well, my parents were rural.

18:54.472 --> 18:56.942
They kept the pigs in my room.

18:58.977 --> 19:02.347
I was 6 before I realized
they weren't related to me.

19:03.181 --> 19:05.081
I'm sorry.

19:06.184 --> 19:09.484
You see, my folks, well,
they named their children and their pets...

19:09.654 --> 19:13.064
...after characters they would read about
in magazines or books.

19:13.223 --> 19:15.093
Dan.

19:16.026 --> 19:19.786
I want my baby named after you.

19:20.597 --> 19:22.657
The real you.

19:23.600 --> 19:25.570
Everybody got their Kool-Aid
for the toast?

19:25.736 --> 19:27.526
MAC: Oh. yeah.
-Where's Benay?

19:27.704 --> 19:30.044
-Hi, everybody.
ALL: Hi.

19:30.207 --> 19:36.077
I'd like for all of you to say hello
to my new son. Reinhold.

19:43.287 --> 19:45.977
-Reinhold?
-Uh-huh.

19:47.824 --> 19:49.994
Reinhold?

19:50.893 --> 19:53.423
Uh, were we interrupting something?

19:53.596 --> 19:56.496
No. not at all.
I was just about to toast to your children.

19:56.666 --> 19:58.426
May they live long and prosper.

19:58.968 --> 20:00.938
ALL:
Cheers.

20:01.604 --> 20:05.604
Ah, and now, if you will excuse me....

20:08.777 --> 20:11.507
Reinhold?

20:32.634 --> 20:34.504
Can we talk?

20:37.472 --> 20:40.032
As you probably know...

20:41.408 --> 20:47.248
...I don't subscribe
to any particular organized religion.

20:50.350 --> 20:53.080
But then maybe neither do you. huh?

20:57.690 --> 20:59.120
[SIGHS]

21:01.561 --> 21:03.691
All right. I confess.

21:04.731 --> 21:07.931
I've had more than my share
of spiritual doubt.

21:08.568 --> 21:13.368
But then I've seen some pretty glaring
examples of man's inhumanity to man...

21:13.539 --> 21:18.239
...come stomping through here
night after night.

21:20.947 --> 21:22.707
After night.

21:27.553 --> 21:29.783
You remember that guy?

21:32.291 --> 21:33.691
Yeah.

21:35.328 --> 21:37.758
You remember everything. don't you?

21:39.431 --> 21:41.491
Well, I'm telling you...

21:41.967 --> 21:44.367
...that one just about shook--

21:44.536 --> 21:48.226
Shook my faith down to its foundation.

21:53.411 --> 21:55.001
And then...

21:57.247 --> 22:04.237
...you drop a brand-new life
right into my hands.

22:06.423 --> 22:08.263
[SIGHS]

22:11.594 --> 22:14.504
Well. if I could just have the answer
to a couple of questions.

22:14.664 --> 22:19.234
Like. if you've always been here.
then where did you come from?

22:20.870 --> 22:26.640
And does man have the capacity
to rid himself of his own evil?

22:32.015 --> 22:34.505
And why is the sky blue?

22:36.920 --> 22:39.360
Well, I can look that one up.

22:41.825 --> 22:44.725
But this baby stuff. boy...

22:45.295 --> 22:50.095
...I'm telling you.
that is not a cosmic accident.

22:50.633 --> 22:53.003
I mean, you gave us Mozart.

22:55.505 --> 22:57.265
Van Gogh.

23:00.443 --> 23:02.243
Confucius.

23:04.213 --> 23:06.583
Dr. Martin Luther King.

23:10.052 --> 23:12.382
And Larry Byrd.

